{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d659300f-d506-49bc-8f1f-15faf785f917","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, VSTest options move to native MTP flags passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Tag=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Mapping:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/*[Tag=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Required project property** (for `dotnet test` to route to MTP on .NET 8):\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\n> **Note:** The treenode filter syntax depends on your framework. `Tag=Integration` works for MSTest's `[TestCategory(\"Integration\")]`. For xUnit traits, adjust accordingly (e.g., `/**/*[Category=Integration]`). You can discover the tree with `--list-tests` to verify the filter matches.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e34c857a-af46-420b-b922-9444a22c8c7e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage) or you use a runsettings\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the execution model differs from VSTest—you typically run tests through `dotnet run` or the built executable rather than `dotnet test`. However, there's a compatibility layer that allows `dotnet test` to work with the new platform. Starting with .NET 9 SDK, `dotnet test` has built-in integration with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but for .NET 8, you'd need to use `dotnet run --project` or enable MSBuild integration.\n\nNow I'm looking at the actual command mappings. When using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you pass arguments after `--`, and the filter syntax changes from VSTest expressions to a different format. If running the test executable directly, you'd use `dotnet run --project` with the new argument structure, including the updated filter syntax and the renamed hang/crash dump options. The other command equivalents map similarly: `--crashdump` for crash handling, `--hangdump` with timeout for hang detection, all requiring their respective extension packages. For .NET 8 specifically, since native Microsoft.Testing.Platform support isn't built into `dotnet test` yet, I'd need to either pass arguments through the `--` separator or run the test project directly, and I should verify the exact setup requirements around NuGet packages and project configuration. I'm realizing the filter syntax varies depending on whether I'm using VSTest or Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly, and it also differs between MSTest and xUnit. For .NET 8, I should focus on the practical approach with the right property to enable the testing platform, then show the actual command that works.","outputTokens":1878,"requestId":"67E1:20EF54:2A4F568:2E9C683:69FD34A6"},"id":"0a5850a1-b7a5-4f32-a7c5-daf520a2f2ff","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:41.036Z","parentId":"8e8b5bb4-394c-40c9-b16f-924dd97c7ae9"}
